---
title: SecurityClaw — Autonomous AI Penetration Testing Platform
description: SecurityClaw is an autonomous AI pentesting platform with 56 integrated tools, 272 unit tests, and 11 consecutive 100% E2E pass campaigns. See live tool scorecard.
layout: base.njk
permalink: /securityclaw/
---
<style>
  .sc-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 50%, #0f3460 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .sc-hero h1 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .sc-hero .tagline { color: #a8c7fa; font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .sc-badge-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.6rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .sc-badge {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.9rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #e8f4f8;
  }
  .sc-badge.green { background: rgba(34,197,94,0.2); border-color: rgba(34,197,94,0.4); color: #86efac; }
  .sc-stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .sc-stat-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.2rem 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .sc-stat-card .sc-number {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0f3460;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .sc-stat-card .sc-label {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: #64748b;
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .sc-scorecard { margin: 2rem 0; }
  .sc-scorecard h2 { border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .sc-category-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .sc-category-table th {
    background: #f8fafc;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
    color: #475569;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .sc-category-table td { padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f5f9; }
  .sc-category-table tr:hover td { background: #f8fafc; }
  .sc-pass-bar {
    height: 8px;
    background: #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    min-width: 80px;
  }
  .sc-pass-bar-fill { height: 100%; background: #22c55e; border-radius: 4px; }
  .sc-pass-bar-fill.partial { background: #f59e0b; }
  .sc-pass-bar-fill.fail { background: #ef4444; }
  .sc-pct { font-weight: 600; color: #16a34a; }
  .sc-pct.fail { color: #dc2626; }
  .sc-pct.partial { color: #d97706; }
  .sc-tools-list { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #64748b; }
  .sc-no-data {
    text-align: center; padding: 2rem; color: #94a3b8;
    border: 1px dashed #cbd5e1; border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .sc-e2e-record {
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f0fdf4 0%, #dcfce7 100%);
    border: 1px solid #86efac;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .sc-e2e-record h3 { color: #15803d; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .sc-e2e-record p { color: #166534; font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0; }
  .sc-cta {
    background: #0f3460;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .sc-cta a { color: #93c5fd; }
  .sc-meta { font-size: 0.78rem; color: #94a3b8; margin-top: 1rem; }
</style>

<div class="sc-hero">
  <h1>SecurityClaw™</h1>
  <div class="tagline">Autonomous AI Penetration Testing Platform</div>
  <div class="sc-badge-row">
    <span class="sc-badge green">✅ 272 Unit Tests Passing</span>
    <span class="sc-badge green">✅ 11× Consecutive 100% E2E</span>
    <span class="sc-badge">🔧 56 Tools Integrated</span>
    <span class="sc-badge">🔐 Active Development</span>
  </div>
</div>

<article>

  <section id="platform-stats">
    <h2>Platform Health</h2>
    <div class="sc-stats-grid">
      <div class="sc-stat-card">
        <div class="sc-number">272</div>
        <div class="sc-label">Unit Tests Passing</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-stat-card">
        <div class="sc-number">11×</div>
        <div class="sc-label">Consecutive 100% E2E</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-stat-card">
        <div class="sc-number">56</div>
        <div class="sc-label">Tools Integrated</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-stat-card">
        <div class="sc-number">26</div>
        <div class="sc-label">Findings per Campaign</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-stat-card">
        <div class="sc-number">9</div>
        <div class="sc-label">E2E Test Scenarios</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-stat-card">
        <div class="sc-number">{{ securityclaw_scorecard.total_campaigns }}</div>
        <div class="sc-label">Campaigns Logged</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sc-e2e-record">
      <h3>🏆 11 Consecutive 100% E2E Pass Campaigns</h3>
      <p>Every end-to-end campaign since integration has passed all 9 test scenarios — 11 straight, zero failures. 11 tools running per campaign, 26 findings identified, 18 correlation patterns mapped per run.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sc-scorecard" id="scorecard">
    <h2>Live Tool Scorecard</h2>
    <p>Campaign result data pulled directly from the SecurityClaw database. Updated automatically after each campaign run.</p>

    {% if securityclaw_scorecard.total_campaigns > 0 %}

      {% if securityclaw_scorecard.overall_pass_rate %}
      <p style="margin: 0.8rem 0;"><strong>Overall pass rate:</strong>
        <span class="sc-pct">{{ (securityclaw_scorecard.overall_pass_rate * 100) | round }}%</span>
        across {{ securityclaw_scorecard.total_campaigns }} campaign{{ 's' if securityclaw_scorecard.total_campaigns != 1 else '' }}
      </p>
      {% endif %}

      <table class="sc-category-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Campaigns</th>
            <th>Pass Rate</th>
            <th>Pass</th>
            <th>Partial</th>
            <th>Fail</th>
            <th>Tools</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for cat, stats in securityclaw_scorecard.categories %}
          <tr>
            <td><strong>{{ cat }}</strong></td>
            <td>{{ stats.campaigns_run }}</td>
            <td>
              {% if stats.pass_rate != null %}
              <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:0.5rem;">
                <div class="sc-pass-bar">
                  <div class="sc-pass-bar-fill" style="width:{{ (stats.pass_rate * 100) | round }}%"></div>
                </div>
                <span class="sc-pct">{{ (stats.pass_rate * 100) | round }}%</span>
              </div>
              {% else %}
              <span style="color:#94a3b8">—</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td>
              {% if stats.pass_rate != null %}
              <span style="color:#16a34a; font-weight:600;">{{ (stats.pass_rate * 100) | round }}%</span>
              {% else %}—{% endif %}
            </td>
            <td>
              {% if stats.partial_rate != null and stats.partial_rate > 0 %}
              <span style="color:#d97706; font-weight:600;">{{ (stats.partial_rate * 100) | round }}%</span>
              {% else %}—{% endif %}
            </td>
            <td>
              {% if stats.fail_rate != null and stats.fail_rate > 0 %}
              <span style="color:#dc2626; font-weight:600;">{{ (stats.fail_rate * 100) | round }}%</span>
              {% else %}—{% endif %}
            </td>
            <td class="sc-tools-list">{{ stats.tools | join(', ') }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>

    {% else %}
      <div class="sc-no-data">
        <p>Campaign data not yet available in this view. Check back after campaigns are logged via the API.</p>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <p class="sc-meta">Data generated: {{ securityclaw_scorecard.generated_at | replace("T", " ") | replace("+00:00", " UTC") | replace(".000000+00:00", " UTC") }}</p>
  </section>

  <section id="what-it-does">
    <h2>What SecurityClaw Does</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Full kill chain automation</strong> — from passive recon to post-exploitation, orchestrated by AI agents that reason about what they find and adapt accordingly</li>
      <li><strong>56 real security tools</strong> — nmap, masscan, gobuster, Nuclei, Nikto, SQLmap, Metasploit, Hydra, Hashcat, Sliver, Burp Suite, TruffleHog, WPScan, and more</li>
      <li><strong>Persistent findings database</strong> — every finding stored and searchable across campaigns. Nothing disappears when a session ends</li>
      <li><strong>Continuous coverage</strong> — runs 24/7 autonomously, catching regressions before attackers do</li>
      <li><strong>Attack path reporting</strong> — not just a list of CVEs. A narrative of how an attacker would move through your environment</li>
      <li><strong>Live scorecard API</strong> — <code>GET /scorecard</code> returns real performance data per tool category, feeding this page automatically</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="who-its-for">
    <h2>Who It's For</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Security consultants</strong> — run more assessments per week; eliminate tool coordination overhead</li>
      <li><strong>In-house security teams</strong> — continuous coverage between annual pentests, automatic regression detection after deployments</li>
      <li><strong>CISOs</strong> — board-level reporting on actual exploitability, not CVSS counts; evidence for SOC 2, PCI DSS, ISO 27001</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="notify">
    <div class="sc-cta">
      <h2 style="color:#fff; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Early Access</h2>
      <p style="color:#cbd5e1; margin-bottom:1rem;">SecurityClaw is in active development and approaching commercial release. If you want early access or want to be notified at launch:</p>
      <p><strong><a href="mailto:info@bughuntertools.com">info@bughuntertools.com</a></strong></p>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Read more about the problem SecurityClaw is solving:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/articles/why-your-security-scanner-isnt-a-penetration-test/">Why Your Security Scanner Isn't a Penetration Test</a></li>
      <li><a href="/articles/automated-penetration-testing-guide-2026/">The Complete Guide to Automated Penetration Testing in 2026</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</article>
